When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
to share projects or if i work on more than one place/computer

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
Sometimes, another user might have updated the github folder but I don't want these changes for my local version.

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
forks -> make a copy of an online reposotory into your github account
clone -> make a copy of an online/offline reposotory into your local machines
branch -> create a new branch on th reposotory which you are using whether it's online or offline

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote stored locally?
Knowing last online interaction is beneficial to predict the output of any command done in the future

How would you collaborate without using Git or GitHub? What would be easier, and what would be harder?
Dropbox, FInding means to explain what each member did would be much harder and evaluating merges and changes would be extremly harder
easier to use and better interface and explaination